f=Executive Office/vista/marketplace/rice-prioritization/references/example.md · h1:Example: rice-prioritization=**You invoke with:** "Run RICE our backlog know what build first" **It needs you:** · h1:Example: rice-prioritization=INITIATIVES (required): "Six items: SSO/SAML login, in-app onboarding checklist, mobile push notifications, CSV bulk import, usage-based billing tier, dark mode.", GOAL (optional): "Lift quarterly activations (new users who complete first project).", CONTEXT (optional): "We analytics signup-to-activation funnels, 6-person eng team, SSO already committed one enterprise deal closing quarter." · h1:Example: rice-prioritization=**You get back:** saved markdown report (`rice-prioritization-<backlog>-<date>.md`) calibration front, ranked RICE table (Reach, Impact, Confidence, Effort, score), per-item rationale, sensitivity note flagging fragile rankings validate-before-committing bets, recommended roadmap order. **See full worked example:** [rice-prioritization-q3-backlog-2026-06-19.md](rice-prioritization-q3-backlog-2026-06-19.md), report invocation produces.